{
  "local_port": 54822,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm on Jio network. I am able to watch Youtube videos cleanly without much buffering but downloading speed is pathetic",
  "response": "If you're experiencing good streaming performance but poor download speeds on your Jio network, there could be several factors at play. Here are a few potential causes and solutions to consider:\n\n### Factors and Solutions\n\n1. **Network Congestion:**\n   - **Cause:** High number of users on the network can lead to congestion, affecting download speeds more significantly than buffered streaming which can adjust quality.\n   - **Solution:** Try downloading during off-peak hours, such as early morning or late at night.\n\n2. **Throttle Limits:**\n   - **Cause:** ISPs sometimes prioritize streaming services over downloads, resulting in lower download speeds.\n   - **Solution:** Check with Jio customer support if there are any data throttling policies on your current plan.\n\n3. **Plan Limitations:**\n   - **Cause:** Your data plan might have specific limitations on download speeds.\n   - **Solution:** Review your plan details to ensure it supports high-speed downloads. Upgrading your plan might help.\n\n4. **Device Settings:**\n   - **Cause:** Device settings or apps running in the background might be affecting download speed.\n   - **Solution:** Ensure that no background apps or system updates are consuming bandwidth. You can also try restarting your device or the app you are using for downloads.\n\n5. **Server Issues:**\n   - **Cause:** The server from which you're downloading might be experiencing high traffic or issues.\n   - **Solution:** Try downloading from a different source or server if possible.\n\n6. **Wi-Fi vs. Mobile Data:**\n   - **Cause:** If you\u2019re using Wi-Fi, the signal strength or configuration might be at fault.\n   - **Solution:** If you're on Wi-Fi, ensure that you are close to the router, or try using mobile data directly to see if the speeds improve.\n\n7. **App or Browser Limitations:**\n   - **Cause:** Sometimes, the app or browser you\u2019re using to download files could be causing slow downloads.\n   - **Solution:** Try using a different browser or download manager app to see if speeds improve.\n\n8. **Network Settings:**\n   - **Cause:** Incorrect network settings can affect download speeds.\n   - **Solution:** Check your APN settings for Jio to ensure they are configured correctly.\n\nIf none of these solutions resolve your issue, contacting Jio customer support may provide more specific guidance or technical support.",
